(42, 2, 20, 19, 72, 17, 19, 'glorifying and praising God', 'Connection of Praise and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize glorifying God and His wondrous works. The shepherds'' praise in Luke reflects the blessings and glory attributed to God in Psalms.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 20, 23, 29, 19, 19, 'glorifying and praising God', 'Joy and Praise Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy and praise in both passages. The shepherds'' glorifying and praising God in Luke parallels the rejoicing of the meek and poor in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 20, 44, 11, 18, 18, 'glorifying and praising God', 'Glorifying God in Response', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to significant revelations. The shepherds glorify God for what they have seen and heard, while the believers in Acts glorify God upon realizing His grace extends to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 20, 40, 9, 8, 8, 'glorifying and praising God', 'Glorifying God in Response', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to miraculous events. The shepherds glorify God for what they heard and saw, while the multitudes marvel and glorify God for the power given to men.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
