(42, 2, 21, 1, 17, 12, 12, 'eight days were accomplished for the circumcising', 'Circumcision and Naming of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the significance of the eighth day for circumcision in both passages. Luke 2:21 mentions the circumcision of Jesus on the eighth day, paralleling Genesis 17:12, which establishes the practice of circumcision for male children at eight days old.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 42, 1, 31, 31, 'his name was called JESUS', 'Naming of Jesus Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the naming of Jesus, with Luke 1:31 stating the name to be given and Luke 2:21 confirming its use at circumcision. This connection highlights the fulfillment of the angel''s announcement regarding the child''s name.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 3, 12, 3, 3, NULL, 'Circumcision on the Eighth Day', 'This connection highlights the significance of the eighth day for circumcision in both passages. Luke 2:21 confirms that Jesus was circumcised on the eighth day, as prescribed in Leviticus 12:3.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 42, 1, 59, 59, NULL, 'Eighth Day Circumcision Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the eighth day for circumcision. They highlight the naming of the child during this ritual, connecting Jesus'' naming to the Jewish tradition.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 48, 4, 4, 5, 'his name was called JESUS', 'Connection of Jesus'' Naming and Law', 'This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' name and his role under the law. Both passages emphasize the divine purpose of Jesus'' birth and his mission to redeem those under the law.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 40, 1, 21, 21, 'his name was called JESUS', 'Naming of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the name ''JESUS'' and its significance. Luke 2:21 states the name was given as instructed by the angel, while Matthew 1:21 explains the purpose of this name in relation to salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 21, 40, 3, 15, 15, NULL, 'Fulfillment of Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of fulfilling divine commands. In Luke, Jesus is named as instructed by the angel, while in Matthew, he speaks of fulfilling all righteousness through his actions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 22, 3, 12, 1, 8, 'the days of her purification', 'Purification and Presentation Rituals', 'Both passages emphasize the purification process after childbirth and the presentation of the child to the Lord. Luke 2:22 refers to the fulfillment of the purification days as outlined in Leviticus 12:1-8, which details the requirements for a woman after giving birth.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
