(42, 2, 23, 4, 18, 15, 15, 'Every male that openeth the womb', 'Connection of Firstborn Concepts', 'This connection highlights the significance of the firstborn in both passages. Luke 2:23 refers to every male that opens the womb as holy, paralleling Numbers 18:15, which discusses the firstborn of man and the requirement of redemption.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
