(42, 2, 24, 3, 12, 6, 8, 'A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.', 'Sacrificial Offerings Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the requirement of offering a pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons as a sacrifice. This connection highlights the provision in Leviticus for those unable to afford a lamb, which is reflected in Luke''s account of Jesus'' presentation.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
