(42, 2, 24, 47, 8, 9, 9, 'A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons', 'Connection of Sacrifice and Poverty', 'This connection highlights the theme of sacrifice, where the offering of turtledoves in Luke symbolizes humility and poverty. Similarly, 2 Corinthians emphasizes Jesus'' choice to become poor for the sake of others, linking both passages through the concept of sacrificial giving.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
